I"J<h1 id="aaba-song-form">AABA song form</h1>
<p>AABA song form was very popular in American pop and jazz music from the first half of the 20th century. It is comprised of an A section, typically 8 bars, followed by a repetition of A, often with different lyrics, followed by a contrasting B section, followed by a repeat of A.</p>
